==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plat
<hw>Plat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Platted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Platting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See <er>Plait</er>.]</ety>
<def>To form by interlaying interweaving; to braid; to plait.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧They had <xex>platted</xex> a crown of thorns.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Matt. xxvii. 29.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Plat
<hw>Plat</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Work done by platting or braiding; a
plait.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her hair, nor loose, nor tied in formal <qex>plat</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Plat
<hw>Plat</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Plat</er> flat, which perh.
caused this spelling, and <er>Plot</er> a piece of ground.]</ety> <def>A
small piece or plot of ground laid out with some design, or for a
special use; usually, a portion of flat, even ground.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This flowery <qex>plat</qex>, the sweet recess of Eve.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I keep smooth <qex>plat</qex> of fruitful ground.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Plat
<hw>Plat</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To lay out in plats or plots, as
ground.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Plat
<hw>Plat</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>plat</ets>. See
<er>Plate</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Plain; flat; level.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Gower.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 6 ====
HEADWORD: Plat
<hw>Plat</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Plainly; flatly;
downright.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But, sir, ye lie, I tell you <qex>plat</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Rom. of
R.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Flatly; smoothly; evenly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Drant.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 7 ====
HEADWORD: Plat
<hw>Plat</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The flat or broad side of
a sword.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A plot; a plan; a design; a diagram; a map; a
chart.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧To note all the
islands, and to set them down in <xex>plat</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hakluyt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Platan</ent>⟦br⟧
